d><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>92</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>x</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>y</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>x</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>y</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>88</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math><br><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>x</mi></math></em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>eigenvalue&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> gives</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>x</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>y</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>M1</em></strong> for an attempt to find the eigenvector with eigenvalue <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>eigenvector = eg. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>A0A1M0A0</em></strong> if only <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> is seen and no eigenvalues are found.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4&nbsp; marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22580874","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ2.5d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate eigenvectors for the matrix T.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.19—Transition matrices – Markov chains","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Eigenvalues and eigenvectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}